<sectiontitle>Right triangle trigonometry</sectiontitle>

<image>01001.png</image> 

<para>
A <italic>right triangle</italic> is defined as having one angle precisely equal to 90<superscript>o</superscript> (a <italic>right angle</italic>).
</para>


<subsection>
<subsectiontitle>Trigonometric identities</subsectiontitle>

<index>Trigonometric identities</index>

<image>11034.png</image> 

<index>Hypotenuse</index>
